CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FMeningococcal disease is serious and
OL,7,Fcan progress rapidly, but it is still
OL,8,Frare, and outbreaks have become much
OL,9,Frarer with improved vaccination
OL,10,Fprogrammes and public awareness.
OL,12,FWhat you need to know about meningitis
OL,13,F` including symptoms, risks and how to
OL,14,Fprotect yourself.
OL,16,FWhat is meningitis and who can it
OL,17,Faffect?
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FMeningitis is inflammation of the
OL,7,Fmembranes that surround the brain and
OL,8,Fspinal cord. It can be caused by
OL,9,Fviruses or bacteria, but the most
OL,10,Fserious cases are often caused by the
OL,11,Fbacterium Neisseria meningitidis.
OL,13,FAnyone can get meningitis, but it is
OL,14,Fmost commonly caught by babies, young
OL,15,Fchildren, teenagers and young adults.
OL,17,FThis is due in part to people in this
OL,18,Fage group carrying the bacteria in the
OL,19,Fnose or throat without symptoms.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FThe bacteria that cause meningococcal
OL,7,Fmeningitis are often carried
OL,8,Fharmlessly in the nose and throat;
OL,9,Faround 10% of the general population
OL,10,Fcarries them without ever becoming
OL,11,Fill. In adolescents and young adults,
OL,12,Fcarriage can be higher, with large UK
OL,13,Fstudies showing rates between 7% and
OL,14,F18%.
OL,16,FTransmission requires close, prolonged
OL,17,Fcontact such as coughing, sneezing or
OL,18,Fkissing, and even among carriers only
OL,19,Fa very small proportion ever develops
OL,20,Finvasive disease.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FOutbreaks usually happen when a
OL,7,Fparticular meningococcal strain enters
OL,8,Fa community where people are mixing
OL,9,Fclosely, such as a university, which
OL,10,Fcreates an environment where the
OL,11,Fbacteria can spread more easily.
OL,13,FWhat are the symptoms of meningitis?
OL,15,FSymptoms of meningitis can look
OL,16,Fsimilar to common illnesses like a
OL,17,Fcold or flu, however, someone with
OL,18,Fmeningitis will usually become
OL,19,Fseriously ill in a matter of hours.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FSymptoms can include fever, seizures,
OL,7,Fvomiting, headache, a stiff neck, or a
OL,8,Frash that does not fade when a glass
OL,9,Fis pressed against it.
OL,11,FSome people may also become drowsy,
OL,12,Funresponsive or sensitive to bright
OL,13,Flights.
OL,15,FSymptoms can appear in any order and
OL,16,Fmay not always be present at once.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FThe UK Health Security Agency advises
OL,7,Fcalling 999 immediately or going to
OL,8,Fyour nearest A&E if you think you or
OL,9,Fsomeone in your care could have
OL,10,Fmeningitis or septicaemia, as people
OL,11,Fcan become unwell very quickly.
OL,13,FYou can call NHS 111 if you're unsure
OL,14,Fwhether it's serious.
OL,16,FWhat causes meningitis and how does it
OL,17,Fspread?
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FIn most cases, meningitis is caused by
OL,7,Fa viral or bacterial infection. Viral
OL,8,Fmeningitis is more common and
OL,9,Ftypically less serious, often getting
OL,10,Fbetter within 7 to 10 days.
OL,12,FMeanwhile, bacterial meningitis is
OL,13,Frare but can be life-threatening.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FDr Zina Alfahl, School of Medicine,
OL,7,FUniversity of Galway, says outbreaks
OL,8,Fare usually driven by a combination of
OL,9,Ffactors, "the characteristics of the
OL,10,Fstrain itself, the level of immunity
OL,11,Fin the population, and environmental
OL,12,Ffactors like crowded living or social
OL,13,Fsettings where people mix intensively".
OL,15,FUsually, the meningitis is spread by
OL,16,Fpeople who are not ill themselves, but
OL,17,Frather carry the viruses or bacteria
OL,18,Fin their nose or throat.
OL,20,FIn some cases, it can be spread by
OL,21,Fsomeone with meningitis.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FThe UKHSA says that "very
OL,7,Foccasionally" meningococcal bacteria
OL,8,Fcan cause serious illness, including
OL,9,Finflammation of the lining of the
OL,10,Fbrain and blood poisoning, which can
OL,11,Frapidly lead to sepsis.
OL,13,FWhat can people do to protect
OL,14,Fthemselves from meningitis?
OL,16,FDr Alfahl says that the most
OL,17,F"important thing is recognising
OL,18,Fsymptoms early and seeking medical
OL,19,Fhelp quickly".
OL,26,@nD@UOUoD@MO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G10/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
