OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FEarly symptoms can look like flu but
OL,7,Fpeople should seek urgent medical
OL,8,Fadvice if symptoms worsen or if there
OL,9,Fare warning signs such as neck
OL,10,Fstiffness, confusion, sensitivity to
OL,11,Flight, or a rash that doesn't fade
OL,12,Fwhen pressed.
OL,14,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,15,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,16,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,17,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,19,FIs there a vaccine for meningitis, and
OL,20,Fhow do I know if I've had one?
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41612
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FSeveral vaccines protect against
OL,7,Fdifferent meningococcal groups,
OL,8,Fincluding MenB and MenACWY. Other
OL,9,Froutine childhood vaccines, such as
OL,10,Fthe 6-in-1 vaccine and MMR, protect
OL,11,Fagainst infections that can also cause
OL,12,Fmeningitis.
OL,14,FThe pneumococcal vaccine is offered to
OL,15,Fbabies in two doses or a single dose
OL,16,Fto adults aged 65 or over.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G12/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41613
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FTeenagers, sixth formers and freshers
OL,7,Fattending university for the first
OL,8,Ftime can have the MenACWY vaccine,
OL,9,Fwhich can help protect against
OL,10,Fmeningitis and sepsis.
OL,12,F"Vaccination remains the best
OL,13,Fprotection. The MenACWY and MenB
OL,14,Fvaccines used in the UK are safe,
OL,15,Fwelltested, and available free to
OL,16,Feligible UK and international
OL,17,Fstudents," said Dr Simon Clarke,
OL,18,FAssociate Professor of Cellular
OL,19,FMicrobiology, University of Reading.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G13/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41614
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FThe MenACWY vaccine can be given up to
OL,7,Fthe age of 25 if it has been missed
OL,8,Fand is also available to some
OL,9,Findividuals who are at greater risk
OL,10,Fdue to a medical condition, work,
OL,11,Ftravel or close contact with someone
OL,12,Fwho is infected.
OL,14,FIf you are unsure if you or your child
OL,15,Fhas been vaccinated, you can speak to
OL,16,Fyour GP.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G14/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41615
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FWhile the NHS offers vaccinations to
OL,7,Fthose most at risk, private
OL,8,Fvaccinations are available at some
OL,9,Ftravel clinics, private GP practices
OL,10,Fand pharmacies.
OL,12,FDr Alfahl said the meningococcal
OL,13,Fvaccines used in the UK are "highly
OL,14,Feffective, particularly the MenACWY
OL,15,Fvaccine given to teenagers".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G15/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41616
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,F"Uptake in adolescents is generally
OL,7,Fgood ` around 70`75% in recent school
OL,8,Fcohorts ` although it hasn't fully
OL,9,Freturned to pre-pandemic levels...
OL,10,FHowever, many current university
OL,11,Fstudents were born before the infant
OL,12,FMenB programme began in 2015, which
OL,13,Fmeans some of them may never have been
OL,14,Froutinely offered that vaccine."
OL,16,FWhat other ways can I help protect
OL,17,Fmyself from meningitis?
OL,19,FIt is a good habit to practice
OL,20,Fhandwashing hygiene, washing your
OL,21,Fhands after coughing or sneezing.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G16/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41617
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FYou can also avoid sharing items which
OL,7,Fcome into contact with your mouth,
OL,8,Fsuch as food, drink and eating
OL,9,Futensils.
OL,11,FRegularly cleaning surfaces can also
OL,12,Fhelp reduce the spread of germs.
OL,14,FWhat measures are being taken in Kent?
OL,16,FThe UK Health Security Agency and the
OL,17,FNHS are now arranging antibiotics for
OL,18,Fsome students at the University of
OL,19,FKent, following the outbreak there.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G17/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41618
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FTrish Mannes, UKHSA regional deputy
OL,7,Fdirector for the South East, said:
OL,8,F"Students and staff will
OL,9,Funderstandably be feeling worried
OL,10,Fabout the risk of further cases;
OL,11,Fhowever, we would like to reassure
OL,12,Fthem that close contacts of cases have
OL,13,Fbeen given antibiotics as a
OL,14,Fprecautionary measure."
OL,16,FYou can read more about the advice
OL,17,Fissued to University of Kent students
OL,18,Fhere.
OL,20,FHow is meningitis treated?
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G18/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41619
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FPeople with suspected meningitis may
OL,7,Fhave to have hospital tests to get a
OL,8,Fdiagnosis and find out if their
OL,9,Fillness is a viral or bacterial
OL,10,Finfection.
OL,12,FBacterial meningitis usually requires
OL,13,Fhospital treatment for at least a
OL,14,Fweek, including antibiotics, fluids
OL,15,Fand oxygen.
OL,17,FShould students be especially careful?
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G19/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41620
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FAccess to vaccinations has meant
OL,7,Foutbreaks are more unusual; however,
OL,8,Fmeningitis can spread rapidly in
OL,9,Fplaces like universities and colleges.
OL,11,FTom Nutt, chief executive of
OL,12,FMeningitis Now, says: "University
OL,13,Fstudents and young adults are among
OL,14,Fthe groups at increased risk because
OL,15,Fmeningitis bacteria can spread more
OL,16,Feasily in settings where people live,
OL,17,Fstudy and socialise closely together."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G20/22
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41621
SC,0021
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1773684358
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FTrish Mannes, UKHSA regional deputy
OL,7,Fdirector for the South East, adds:
OL,8,F"Students are particularly at risk of
OL,9,Fmissing the early warning signs of
OL,10,Fmeningitis because they can be easily
OL,11,Fconfused with other illnesses such as
OL,12,Fa bad cold, flu or even a hangover.
OL,14,F"That's why it's vital that, if a
OL,15,Ffriend goes to bed unwell, you check
OL,16,Fon them regularly and don't hesitate
OL,17,Fto seek medical help by contacting
OL,18,Ftheir GP or calling NHS 111 if they
OL,19,Fhave these symptoms or you're
OL,20,Fconcerned about them. This could save
OL,21,Ftheir life."
